article.headline: Princeton 58, Yale 45
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Douglas Davis scored 13 points and Princeton held off Yale 58-45 on Saturday night for the Tigers' ninth win in 10 games. The first half was close, with Princeton (11-5, 2-0 Ivy League) leading 32-27 at halftime. The Tigers then went on a 7-2 run to lead 39-29 with 17:10 left, but the Bulldogs (8-13, 2-2) used an 9-0 spurt to tie the game at 39 with 10 minutes to go. Princeton responded with a 9-1 run, then Alex Zampier hit a jumper with 6:26 left to make the score 48-42 with 6:26 left. Yale did not make another field goal the rest of the game. The Tigers outshot the Bulldogs from the field 51.1 percent (23-for-45) to 35.3 percent (14-for-40) for Yale, which was only 6-for-23 in the second half. The Bulldogs made 14 of 20 free throws. Princeton scored 18 points off 14 turnovers. Michael Sands led Yale with 14 points and Zampier added 13.
